 Thuso Mbedu has bagged her second international Emmy nomination. The SAFTA award-winning actress has once again been nominated for her role in the second season of the Mzansi Magic drama, Is'thunzi. Thuso has been nominated in the Best Actress category and will go up against other actresses from Brazil, Germany and the UK. The 27-year-old shared the exciting news on Twitter saying: “A 2-time International Emmy nominee. Wow.”  She also posted a glamour picture of herself and said the last time she #WCW (woman crushed Wednesday) herself she got an “iEmmy nomination.”   View tweet HERE The 46th International Emmy Awards ceremony will be held on 19 November at the Hilton Hotel in New York.      